				<td colspan="2"><span>Well the way eq2 is made, for the first 10 level there is only 4 classes. For 10-20 you got now 12 classeswith half there ability shared with 1/4 of other class. then after level 20 you got 24 class. Lots of class granted, but each of them share almost half of is life span new ability with many other class. So all in all it destroy the difference between each class.
<br />

<br />
When the game will be 6-12 months old, the majority will start to be made of ppl who have choosen a class and get it to the top level. Dont forget until they reach level 41, half of what they learned is share by another class.
<br />

<br />
I think its a flaw in the gameplay. but on the other hand it make it much more easier to balance classes since they kind of all the same.
<br />

<br />
So maybe when there is gonna be 50 Troubadour and 50 Dirge at level 50 per server, maybe someone will feel like making is own site for its class.. but well.. would he make one only for Troubadour with enough content not repeated on a Dirge website ?</span></td>
