				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: ??? EQ2 ???<a name="72196"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 19 05 1:09 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Other comments I'd make...
<br />

<br />
Gear doesn't seem to make that much difference. I have made some huge (over 100 ac) upgrades and barely noticed them.
<br />

<br />
Ability/song/weapon upgrades seem more noticeable.
<br />

<br />
Consequently twinking doesnt seen to be as big an issue so far.
<br />

<br />
There are a lot of tradeskill supplied items that are near necessities. That is good, I think, but I am not sure I'm gonna do a lot of tradeskilling. (29 toon, lvl 14 tradeskiller). I find it much easier to raise the money and buy from others. 
<br />

<br />
Scherzo, you will be happy to know my bazaar whore mentality has followed me to EQII. I have a vendor mule up most of the time. 
<br />

<br />
Boxing in EQII is too hard for me in large group...I would avoid boxers whose capabilities were unknown to me. 
<br />

<br />
I think they delivered on there promise for soloability, for those who want it. Doable by everyone, but not as rewarding.
<br />

<br />
