				<td colspan="2"><span>As you get more defining abilities, it seems you have more tactical choices. I spend a lot of time in undersized groups...an on the edge balanced attack of just enough healing, just enough dps, just enough debuffing seems necessary to survive really tuff fights. 
<br />

<br />
If we overdo one and neglect another, it seems to come back and bite us.
<br />

<br />
I also like the ability to overlap. You had to really work and alter strategy for say, a two bard group in EQI. In EQII, each toon has so much they can do, its pretty easy for each to work his/her full potential and not step on another of the same class.</span></td>
